g6 6. O-O Bg7 7. d5 Na5 8. Qa4+ c6 9. dxc6 Nxc6 10. Ne5 O-O 11. Nxc6 bxc6 12.
Qxc6 Rb8 13. Nc3 Bb7 14. Qa4 Qc7 15. Be2 Rfd8 16. Rd1 Rxd1+ 17. Qxd1 Ne4 18.
Nb5 Qa5 19. f3 Rd8 20. Qf1 {L'Ami,A (2316)-Muhren,B (2290) Novi Sad 2009 1/2-1/
2 (135)}) 6. O-O e6 {Controls d5} 7. a4 (7. Nc3 Be7 $14) 7... Be7 8. Qe2 O-O 9.
Rd1 Na5 10. Ba2 c6 {Covers d5} (10... Nd5 11. Bd2 Nb4 12. Bxb4 Bxb4 13. Qc2 $11
) 11. Bd2 $14 b5 {Black threatens to win material: b5xa4} 12. b4 {White
threatens to win material: b4xa5} Nb7 13. e4 (13. Ne5 Bd7 $14) 13... Qc7 (13...
bxa4 $5 14. Nc3 a3 $14) 14. Bb3 $16 Rd8 15. Na3 a5 16. axb5 axb4 (16... Bxb4
17. e5 Nd5 18. bxc6 Qxc6 19. Rdc1 $16) 17. b6 Qb8 18. Nc4 {[%cal Ye4e5] White
prepares the advance e5} c5 $4 {the position is going down the drain} (18...
Bd7 $142 19. g3 Rxa1 20. Rxa1 c5 $16) 19. Bf4 $1 $18 {[%cal Ye4e5] White
intends e5. Deflection: a8} Nd6 (19... Qxf4 20. Rxa8 {Deflection}) 20. Rxa8 (
20. dxc5 $142 {and White has triumphed} Rxa1 21. Rxa1 Nd7 22. cxd6 Bf8 $18)
20... Qxa8 21. Bxd6 Bxd6 22. e5 Nd5 (22... Be7 {does not improve anything} 23.
exf6 gxf6 24. dxc5 Rxd1+ 25. Bxd1 Bxc5 26. Nfd2 $18) 23. Nxd6 (23. exd6 $142 $5
{keeps an even firmer grip} Nc3 24. Qd3 Nxd1 $18) 23... Nc3 24. Qb2 Nxd1 25.
Bxd1 Qd5 (25... c4 $18) 26. Bb3 Qc6 27. Qc2 Qxb6 28. dxc5 Qc6 (28... Qa6 {
cannot undo what has already been done} 29. h4 Qa1+ 30. Kh2 $18) 29. Nd4 (29.
Ng5 $142 {makes it even easier for White} g6 30. Ngxf7 Rf8 $18) 29... Qa6 30.
h3 Qa1+ 31. Qd1 Qc3 (31... Qxd1+ {a last effort to resist the inevitable} 32.
Bxd1 Rd7 $18) 32. Nc6 Rf8 (32... Rd7 {desperation} 33. Ne7+ $1 {the logical end
} Rxe7 $18) 33. Ne7+ Kh8 34. Nxf7+ $1 {Clearance: d6. . . . .} (34. Nxf7+ Rxf7
35. Qd8+ Rf8 36. Qxf8#) 1-0

