{E91: King's Indian: Classical: 6 Be2, unusual replies including 6...c5 and 6..
.Bg4} 1. d4 g6 2. c4 Bg7 3. Nc3 d6 4. Nf3 Nf6 5. e4 O-O 6. Be2 Nc6 (6... e5 7.
O-O Nc6 8. d5 Nb8 9. Bg5 h6 10. Bh4 a5 (10... Nbd7 11. Nd2 Re8 12. b4 Nf8 13.
f3 g5 14. Bf2 Ng6 15. c5 Nh5 16. g3 Bh3 17. Re1 Rf8 18. Bf1 Bxf1 19. Nxf1 f5
20. Ne3 fxe4 21. fxe4 Nf6 22. Rf1 Qd7 23. Qe2 Qh3 24. Be1 a5 25. Rb1 {Galyas,M
(2413)-Nagy,B (2201) Budapest 2003 1-0 (40)}) 11. c5 Nbd7 12. cxd6 cxd6 13. Nd2
Nc5 14. f3 Bd7 15. a4 Na6 16. Bb5 Nc7 17. Bxd7 Qxd7 18. Nc4 Ra6 19. Qb3 Rb8 20.
Nb5 Nce8 21. Bf2 {Gurevich,M (2540)-Karner,H (2390) Tallinn 1987 1-0 (41)}) 7.
d5 Nb8 8. O-O e5 9. Be3 {Black has a cramped position} Ng4 $146 (9... a5 10.
Nd2 Na6 11. a3 Nd7 12. b4 f5 13. f3 Bf6 14. c5 dxc5 15. bxa5 Bg5 16. Bf2 Be7
17. Nc4 Bd6 18. Nb5 Qe7 19. exf5 gxf5 20. Re1 Qf6 21. Bd3 Kh8 22. Ra2 e4 23.
fxe4 Ne5 24. Nbxd6 {Malaniuk,V (2505)-Csala,I (2320) Budapest 1990 1-0}) 10.
Bg5 Bf6 11. Bxf6 (11. Bd2 Bg7 $14) 11... Nxf6 12. Rc1 Nbd7 13. b4 Kg7 14. c5 {
Nimzovich: attack the chain at its base} (14. a3 a5 $14) 14... h6 {Secures g5}
(14... dxc5 $5 {should be investigated more closely} 15. bxc5 Nxc5 16. Nxe5
Ncxe4 17. Nxe4 Nxe4 $11) 15. cxd6 $16 cxd6 16. Qc2 a6 17. b5 {Black's piece
can't move: c8} (17. Nd2 b5 $16) 17... Nh7 (17... Nh5 18. bxa6 Nf4 19. axb7
Nxe2+ 20. Qxe2 Bxb7 21. Rfe1 $11) 18. bxa6 bxa6 19. Na4 f5 $2 (19... Ndf6 $142
$14 {and Black could well hope to play on}) 20. exf5 $18 gxf5 21. Qc6 Ra7 22.
Qxd6 Rf6 23. Qa3 Ng5 $4 {leading to a quick end} (23... Bb7 24. Rfd1 Ba8 $18)
24. Nxg5 hxg5 25. Rc6 (25. Qe3 $142 {makes it even easier for White} Ra8 26.
Qxg5+ Kf8 $18) 25... Rf8 (25... Rxc6 26. dxc6 Nf8 $18) 26. Rfc1 Ra8 27. Rc7 Kg6
(27... Kg8 {is not much help} 28. R1c6 Rf6 29. d6 $18) 28. R1c6+ (28. Nb6 $142
{seems even better} Rb8 29. Nxc8 Rf6 30. Ne7+ Kg7 $18) 28... Nf6 (28... Rf6 {
doesn't change the outcome of the game} 29. Nb6 $3 {Decoy: b6} Qxc7 30. Rxc7
Rxb6 31. Qe7 $18) 29. Qh3 (29. Bh5+ $142 $1 {secures victory} Kh6 30. Qh3 Qxc7
31. Be8+ Kg7 32. Rxc7+ Bd7 33. Bxd7 Nxd5 34. Rc6 $18) 29... Rh8 30. Qg3 (30.
Qc3 $5 {might be the shorter path} Rb8 31. Qxe5 Rb1+ 32. Bf1 Bb7 33. Rxb7 Rxb7
$18) 30... Bd7 31. Rc3 (31. Rxd7 $142 {and White wins} Qxd7 32. Qxe5 Qxc6 33.
dxc6 $18) 31... Bxa4 (31... Rb8 $142 32. Qd3 Bxa4 33. Qxa6 Ra8 $19) 32. R7c4 $4
{another bit of territory lost} (32. h4 $142 g4 33. R3c4 $17) 32... Bb5 (32...
