Nxd6 17. Ne4 Rd8 18. Rc1 Nf5 19. Rfd1 h5 20. Bb3 Bb7 {Martin,A (2330)-Muir,A 
(2200) London 1979 1-0 (42)}) 6... Nf6 7. O-O e6 8. Ng3 Be7 9. Be3 O-O 10. f4
a6 11. Qe2 b5 12. Bb3 b4 13. Na4 Rb8 14. Rad1 Qa5 15. Bc2 e5 16. h3 exf4 17.
Rxf4 Ne5 18. Nf5 Bxf5 19. Rxf5 Qb5 20. Qf2 {Adnoy,H (2310)-Ni,V (2151)
Pardubice 2009 0-1 (35)}) (5... a6 6. a4 d6 7. Nf3 Nf6 8. h3 e6 9. O-O Be7 10.
Be3 O-O 11. Qe2 Bd7 12. Rfd1 Qc7 13. Bf4 Ne5 14. Nxe5 dxe5 15. Be3 Rac8 16. Bb3
Bc6 17. Rac1 Rfd8 18. f3 Qa5 19. Rxd8+ Rxd8 20. Qc4 {Richter,K (2226)
-Gersinska,J (2295) Germany 1999 0-1 (70)}) 6. Nf3 e5 {Black has a new
backward pawn: d7. Black is behind in developement. Black's piece can't move:
c8} (6... e6 7. Qe2 $11) 7. Ng5 $14 d5 8. exd5 (8. Nxd5 h6 9. Nxf7 Kxf7 10.
Nc7+ Ke7 11. Nxa8 Bd7 $14) 8... Nd4 $11 {A beautiful square!} 9. O-O {White
has a king attack} Bd6 {The bishop blocks d5} 10. Re1 (10. Be3 O-O $11) 10...
O-O $11 {Black castles and improves king safety} 11. Be3 {White threatens to
win material: Be3xd4} Bg4 {Black threatens to win material: Bg4xd1} 12. f3 {
White threatens to win material: f3xg4} Bc8 (12... Rc8 13. Bd3 Bd7 14. Bf2 $11)
13. Bxd4 $14 exd4 14. Qxd4 {Black has the pair of bishops.} Qc7 15. Qh4 (15.
Kh1 Bf5 16. Nb5 Qc5 $16) 15... h6 {Black threatens to win material: h6xg5} 16.
Nge4 Bxh2+ $4 (16... Nxe4 $142 {is the best chance} 17. Nxe4 Bxh2+ 18. Qxh2
Qxc4 $11) 17. Qxh2 $18 Qxc4 18. Nxf6+ gxf6 19. Qxh6 Qd4+ 20. Kh1 (20. Re3 $142
{makes it even easier for White} f5 21. Rd1 $18) 20... Bf5 $4 {Black has lost
his nerve... understandable when you consider his position} (20... f5 $18) 21.
Ne4 (21. Re4 Bxe4 22. Nxe4 f5 23. Qg5+ Kh7 24. Qxf5+ Kg8 25. Qg4+ Kh8 26. Qh4+
Kg7 27. Qg5+ Kh7 28. Nf6+ Qxf6 29. Qxf6 Rg8 30. Qxf7+ Rg7 31. Qf5+ Kg8 32. Qe6+
Kh8 33. Re1 Rf8 34. Re4 Rgf7 35. Qe5+ Rg7 36. Rg4 Rff7 37. Qb8+ Kh7 38. Rh4+
Kg6 39. Qg3+ Kf6 40. Qd6+ Kg5 41. Rg4+ Kh5 42. Qh2#) 21... Bg6 22. Rad1 Qb6 (
22... Qxb2 {cannot change what is in store for White} 23. Rd2 Qe5 24. f4 Qh5+
25. Qxh5 Bxh5 26. Nxf6+ Kg7 27. Nxh5+ Kg6 28. Ng3 $18) 23. d6 Rfe8 (23... Qxb2
