(14) Eltigani,O (2310)-Tatar Kis,S (2367) Hungary 2012}) 5... O-O 6. a3 Bxc3 7.
Bxc3 Ne4 8. e3 Nxc3 9. bxc3 Nd7 10. cxd5 exd5 11. Bd3 Nf6 12. Ne5 Ne4 {Black
threatens to win material: Ne4xc3} 13. Qc2 f5 14. O-O c6 {Consolidates b5} 15.
f3 Nd6 16. Kh1 (16. c4 dxc4 17. Bxc4+ Kh8 $14) 16... Qh4 (16... Be6 17. Rab1
$11) 17. g3 Qh3 (17... Qe7 18. Rab1 $11) 18. Rg1 Be6 19. Bf1 {White threatens
to win material: Bf1xh3} Qh6 {Black threatens to win material: Qh6xe3} 20. Rb1
(20. Re1 Rfc8 $11) 20... Qxe3 21. f4 (21. Bd3 $142 Qh6 22. Rge1 $11) 21... Ne4
$4 {hands over the advantage to the opponent} (21... Qe4+ 22. Rg2 Qxc2 23. Rxc2
$17) 22. Nd3 $4 {gives the opponent new chances} (22. Bd3 $5 Nf2+ 23. Kg2 Nxd3
24. Nxd3 Qe4+ 25. Kf2 c5 $18) 22... Rf7 $4 {with this move Black loses his
initiative} (22... Rf6 23. Ne5 Rh6 24. Kg2 $17) 23. Re1 $4 {White threatens to
win material: Re1xe3. weakening the position} (23. Rg2 $142 {White clearly has
the better chances} Rf6 24. Re1 $16) 23... Qf3+ $15 24. Bg2 (24. Rg2 Qh5 $15)
24... Qh5 {Black has a mate threat} (24... Nxg3+ $5 25. hxg3 Qh5+ 26. Bh3 Qxh3+
27. Qh2 Qxh2+ 28. Kxh2 Re7 $17) 25. Ne5 $4 {solves nothing} (25. Re3 $142 $17)
25... Nxg3# 0-1

