17. Qa3 Qf6 18. h5 gxh5 19. Rfe1 c4 20. e4 dxe4 21. Bxe4 Bxe4 22. Rxe4 Nf8 23.
Qe3 Ra7 {Gevorgyan,D (2395)-Litvinov,M (2192) Moscow 2015 1-0 (35)}) 9... c5
10. Re1 Bb7 11. b3 Ne4 12. Bxe7 {White forks: f8+d8} Qxe7 13. Qc2 Ndf6 (13...
Nxc3 14. Qxc3 dxc4 15. Bxc4 Bxf3 16. gxf3 $15) 14. h3 {Prevents intrusion on g4
} (14. Ne5 Nxc3 15. Qxc3 Rac8 $11) 14... Rad8 (14... Nxc3 15. Qxc3 dxc4 16.
Bxc4 Bxf3 17. gxf3 $15) 15. Rad1 Rc8 (15... Nxc3 16. Qxc3 dxc4 17. Bxc4 Bxf3
18. gxf3 $15) 16. Ne2 (16. Bxe4 Nxe4 17. Nxe4 dxe4 $11) 16... cxd4 17. exd4 Qc7
(17... dxc4 18. bxc4 Nd6 19. Ne5 Nxc4 20. Nxc4 $15) 18. Rc1 Rfd8 19. Red1 Qe7
20. Ne5 dxc4 21. bxc4 {White has new hanging pawns: c4+d4} Qc7 22. f3 {White
threatens to win material: f3xe4} Nd6 (22... Nc5 23. Qb2 Nxd3 24. Rxd3 $11) 23.
Kf2 {White king safety dropped} Nde8 24. g4 (24. c5 bxc5 25. Qxc5 Qb8 $11)
24... Ba6 (24... Rxd4 25. Nxd4 Qxe5 26. Bf1 $15) 25. Rg1 (25. Qa4 $142 Bb7 26.
c5 bxc5 27. Rxc5 $11) 25... Kh8 $4 {not a good decision, because now the
opponent is right back in the game} (25... Rxd4 $142 $1 {would keep Black alive
} 26. Nxd4 Qxe5 $17) 26. g5 {White threatens to win material: g5xf6} (26. Qa4
$142 Bb7 27. c5 bxc5 28. Rxc5 $16) 26... Nh5 $4 (26... hxg5 $142 {had to be
tried to avoid defeat} 27. Rxg5 Kg8 $14) 27. gxh6 $18 g6 $4 {Black crumbles in
face of a dire situation} (27... Rxd4 28. Rg5 Rxd3 29. Qxd3 Nhf6 30. hxg7+ Kg8
$18) 28. Bxg6 $1 {Mate threat} fxg6 (28... fxg6 29. Nxg6+ Kg8 (29... Kh7 30.
Ne7+ {Mate attack}) 30. Ngf4+ {Double attack}) (28... -- $140 29. Bxf7 {
Mate threat}) 29. Qxg6 (29. Nxg6+ $142 {it becomes clear that White will call
all the shots} Kg8 30. Ne7+ Kf8 $18) 29... Rd7 (29... Nef6 {is the last straw}
30. Nf7+ Qxf7 31. Qxf7 Rd7 32. Qxe6 Re8 $18) 30. Qg8# 1-0

