Nc6 6. Bg5 h6 7. Bxf6 Qxf6 8. e3 a5 9. a4 Qg6 10. Nge2 Bxc5 11. Nf4 Qg5 12. Bd3
b6 13. O-O-O Ba6 14. Kb1 Rc8 15. Nb5 Be7 {1/2-1/2 (15) Bhakti,K (2231)
-Narayanan,S (2414) Mumbai 2014}) 4... Nc6 $146 (4... b6 5. b4 a5 6. Ba3 axb4
7. Bxb4 bxc5 8. Bxc5 Bxc5 9. dxc5 Qe7 10. e3 Qxc5 11. Rc1 O-O 12. Ne4 Qa5+ 13.
Qd2 Nxe4 {0-1 (13) Petrov,P (2325)-Vasilev,N (2340) Teteven 1991}) 5. Nf3 h6 {
Consolidates g5} 6. e3 Be7 7. Be2 O-O 8. O-O b6 {Black threatens to win
material: b6xc5} 9. Bb5 {White threatens to win material: Bb5xc6} Bd7 10. Qa4
a5 $4 {gives the opponent counterplay} (10... Qe8 $142 $11 {would save the game
}) 11. Bxc6 $18 Bxc6 (11... bxc5 12. Ne5 Be8 13. Bd2 $18) 12. Qxc6 Qd7 $6 {
offers little resistance} (12... bxc5 13. dxc5 Nd7 14. Na4 $18) 13. Ne5 Qxc6 (
13... Qc8 {does not win a prize} 14. cxb6 cxb6 15. Qxb6 $18) 14. Nxc6 Rfe8 (
14... Bd8 {doesn't change anything anymore} 15. cxb6 cxb6 16. Nb5 $18) 15.
Nxe7+ (15. Nb5 {and White can already relax} Bd8 16. cxb6 cxb6 $18) 15... Rxe7
16. cxb6 cxb6 17. Bd2 Rc7 18. a4 Rb8 19. Rfb1 Rbc8 20. Ra3 (20. f3 {seems even
better} Ra8 $18) 20... Ne8 (20... Ra8 {cannot change what is in store for White
} 21. Kf1 $18) 21. b4 (21. Nb5 {makes it even easier for White} Rc4 $18) 21...
Nd6 22. Rab3 Nc4 23. Be1 Re7 (23... axb4 {does not save the day} 24. Nb5 Re7
25. Rxb4 $18) 24. bxa5 bxa5 25. Nd1 Rec7 26. Nb2 Nxb2 (26... g5 {cannot undo
what has already been done} 27. Nxc4 dxc4 28. Rc3 $18) 27. R3xb2 Rc1 (27... Kh7
{hardly improves anything} 28. Rb5 $18) 28. Rxc1 (28. Rb5 $142 {keeps an even
firmer grip} Rxb1 29. Rxb1 Kf8 $18) 28... Rxc1 29. Kf1 Kh7 (29... Ra1 $18 {
praying for a miracle}) 30. Rb5 g5 31. Rxa5 h5 (31... Kg6 {does not save the
day} 32. Ra7 $18) 32. e4 $1 {Deflection: d5} Kg6 (32... dxe4 33. Re5 {Decoy
Double attack} (33. Rxg5 {Deflection Pinning})) 33. exd5 Rc4 (33... exd5 {
is not the saving move} 34. Rxd5 Ra1 35. a5 $18) 34. dxe6 fxe6 35. Ra8 Rxd4 (
35... Kf5 $18 {desperation}) 36. a5 Ra4 37. a6 Ra2 38. a7 Kf5 39. Rf8+ Ke4 40.
a8=Q+ (40. a8=Q+ Rxa8 41. Rxa8 $18) 1-0

