forks: g7+d8} Qxf6 {Black has the pair of bishops} 12. Bd3 O-O 13. Bxf5 Qxf5
14. O-O Rac8 15. Rc1 Na5 16. Nd2 b5 17. b4 {White threatens to win material:
b4xa5} Nc4 18. Ndb1 (18. Ncb1 Nb2 19. Qe2 Qd3 20. Qxd3 Nxd3 $15) 18... Rc6 $17
19. Rc2 Rfc8 20. Qc1 Nb6 21. Qd2 Kh8 22. Rfc1 Nc4 (22... e5 23. Rd1 $17) 23.
Qe1 Qd3 24. Qe2 Qg6 25. Kh1 f5 26. g3 Rf8 27. Kh2 (27. Nd1 e5 28. dxe5 Bxe5 $15
) 27... Rcc8 (27... h5 28. Qd3 $17) 28. f4 Qe8 29. Nd1 (29. Ra2 Rf7 $17) 29...
Qd7 (29... a5 $5 $17) 30. Nf2 Qb7 31. Nd3 Qb6 32. Nc5 Bxc5 (32... Rfe8 33. Nd2
$11) 33. bxc5 Qc6 34. Rc3 Rb8 35. Rb3 Qc7 36. Nd2 {[%cal Yf3e5,Yd2f3,Yb1d2]
The idea is Nb1-d2-f3-e5} Na5 37. Rb2 Kh7 38. Nf3 Nc4 {Here comes the
goal-getter} 39. Rb3 Qa5 {[%cal Ra5a3,Rc4a3,Gb3a3] Exerts pressure on the
isolated pawn} 40. Ne5 {A beautiful square!} Qa4 {Black threatens to win
material: Qa4xb3} 41. Qd3 Ra8 42. Rcb1 Qa5 43. g4 Qc7 (43... Nxe5 44. fxe5 Kh8
45. gxf5 Rxf5 46. R3b2 $11) 44. gxf5 Rxf5 45. Rg1 (45. Nf3 Na5 46. Nh4 Nxb3 47.
Rxb3 g6 $11) 45... Raf8 (45... Nxe5 46. fxe5 Kg8 47. Rc3 $11) 46. Ng6 $14 {
White threatens to win material: Ng6xf8} R8f6 {Black threatens to win material:
Rf6xg6} (46... R8f7 47. Rg2 $14) 47. Nh4 $16 Kh8 48. Nxf5 Rxf5 (48... exf5 $5
49. Rg3 Kh7 $16) 49. Rg3 g5 (49... Rf8 50. Rb4 $18) 50. Rb1 $18 gxf4 $2 (50...
Qa5 51. Rc1 Qc7 $18) 51. exf4 Rxf4 (51... Qxf4 {does not save the day} 52. Rbg1
$18) 52. Rbg1 (52. Qg6 $142 {keeps an even firmer grip} Rf2+ 53. Kg1 Qxg3+ 54.
Qxg3 Rf7 55. Qb8+ Kh7 $18) 52... Rf2+ (52... Rf6 53. Kh1 Rf8 54. Qg6 Qh7 55.
Qh5 Qe4+ 56. R1g2 Qb1+ 57. Kh2 Qh7 58. Rf3 Qc7+ 59. Kh1 Qg7 60. Rxg7 Kxg7 61.
Qg4+ Kh7 62. Rxf8 h5 63. Qg8+ Kh6 64. Rf6#) 53. R1g2 (53. Kh1 Qf7 54. Rg8+ Qxg8
55. Rxg8+ Kxg8 56. Qg3+ Kf8 57. Qxf2+ Ke7 58. Qh4+ Kd7 59. Qf6 Na5 60. Qf7+ Kd8
61. Qxe6 Kc7 62. Qb6+ Kd7 63. Qxa5 b4 64. axb4 Ke6 65. Qxa6+ Kf5 66. c6 h5 67.
c7 Kg5 68. c8=Q Kf4 69. Qf6+ Ke4 70. Qc2+ Ke3 71. Qff2#) 53... Qf4 (53... Rf6 {
is not the saving move} 54. Kh1 Qf7 55. Rg6 Rf1+ 56. Kh2 $18) 54. Rxf2 Qxf2+
55. Rg2 Qf4+ (55... Qf7 56. Kg1 Na5 57. Qd2 Qf6 58. Qxa5 Qxd4+ 59. Kh1 Qa1+ 60.
Rg1 Qf6 61. Qd2 Kh7 62. Qd3+ Kh8 63. c6 Qg7 64. c7 Qxg1+ 65. Kxg1 Kg7 66. c8=Q
a5 67. Qxe6 d4 68. Qxd4+ Kh7 69. Qf7#) 56. Qg3 Qf7 (56... Qxg3+ {is not much
help} 57. Rxg3 Na5 58. Rg6 $18) 57. Qh4 (57. Kg1 $142 {and the result of the
game is clear: White will win} Kh7 58. c6 h5 $18) 57... Kh7 58. Qg3 (58. Rf2
$142 {secures victory} Qc7+ 59. Kh1 $18) 58... Na5 $4 {weakening the position}
(58... Kh8 59. Kg1 Na5 $18) 59. Qd3+ Kh8 60. Qe3 (60. Kg1 $142 $5 {and White
can already relax} Nc6 $18) 60... Kh7 61. Qd2 {White threatens to win material:
