{C56: Two Knights: 4 d4 exd4 5 0-0 Nxe4} 1. e4 e5 2. Bc4 Nf6 3. d4 Nc6 4. Nf3
exd4 5. e5 Ng4 6. Qe2 Be7 7. h3 Nh6 8. Bxh6 gxh6 9. Nbd2 d5 10. exd6 Qxd6 11.
O-O-O $146 (11. Ne4 Qg6 12. O-O-O Bf5 13. Rhe1 O-O-O 14. g4 Bd7 15. Nxd4 Nxd4
16. Rxd4 Rhe8 17. Kb1 f5 18. gxf5 Bxf5 19. Rxd8+ Kxd8 20. Ng3 Bd7 21. Qf3 Qb6 {
1/2-1/2 (21) Mork,K (2305)-Johannessen,S (2275) Oslo 1998}) 11... Be6 {Black
king safety improved} 12. Rhe1 Bxc4 {Black forks: a2+e2} 13. Qxc4 Qg6 $2 (13...
O-O-O $142 $5 $14 {and Black can hope to survive}) 14. Nxd4 $16 Kf8 (14... Rd8
15. Nxc6 Qxc6 16. Qxc6+ bxc6 17. Re4 $16) 15. Nxc6 (15. N2b3 h5 16. Kb1 h6 $18)
15... bxc6 (15... Qxc6 16. Qxc6 bxc6 17. Nc4 $16) 16. Qe4 (16. Nf3 $142 $5 Bd6
17. Ne5 Qg5+ 18. f4 Qf5 $18) 16... Re8 (16... Qxe4 17. Rxe4 Rg8 18. g3 $16) 17.
Qxg6 (17. Qe5 $5 Rg8 18. g3 $18) 17... hxg6 $14 18. Nc4 Bg5+ 19. Kb1 Rxe1 20.
Rxe1 Kg7 21. c3 Rd8 22. Kc2 h5 (22... Bf6 23. Na5 Rd6 24. Re8 $16) 23. g3 (23.
Re5 Rd5 $16) 23... h4 24. g4 (24. Re4 Rh8 25. g4 Rd8 $16) 24... a6 (24... Bf4
$5 $14) 25. Re4 $16 f5 26. gxf5 gxf5 (26... Rf8 $142 $5 27. f4 gxf5 $16) 27.
Re6 $18 Bf4 28. Rxc6 a5 $2 (28... Re8 29. Kd1 Bg3 $18) 29. Rc5 (29. a4 {
makes it even easier for White} Re8 30. Nxa5 Re2+ 31. Kb3 Bg3 $18) 29... Kf6
30. Rxa5 Re8 31. Kd3 Re1 32. Ne3 $4 {White is ruining his position} (32. Rc5
$142 {White had this great chance} Rh1 33. Ne3 Bxe3 34. Kxe3 $18) 32... Bxe3
$16 33. fxe3 {A rook endgame occured} Rh1 34. Ra8 Rxh3 35. Rh8 Kg7 {Black
threatens to win material: Kg7xh8} 36. Rh5 {White threatens to win material:
Rh5xf5} Kg6 37. Rh8 f4 {Black threatens to win material: f4xe3} 38. Ke2 Rxe3+
39. Kf2 Kg5 40. Rg8+ Kf5 41. Rf8+ Kg4 42. Rg8+ Kf5 43. Rf8+ Ke4 44. Re8+ Kd3
45. Rd8+ Ke4 46. Re8+ Kd3 {Twofold repetition} 47. Rf8 $4 {gives the opponent
counterplay} (47. Rd8+ $142 {and White could well hope to play on} Kc2 48. Rd7
$11) 47... Ke4 $4 {allows the opponent back into the game} (47... h3 $142 {
Black has a promising position} 48. Rxf4 Re2+ 49. Kg1 h2+ 50. Kh1 Rxb2 51. Rf3+
Kc4 52. Rf4+ Kxc3 53. Rf3+ Kb4 54. Rf4+ Kc5 $19) 48. Re8+ $11 1/2-1/2

